2 Tinker Tinker was an Irish Setter. He was red and big and loved to chase sticks and his red ball. Because he was an Irish Setter, his nature was to be a bit crazy and goofy. He showed the girl what it was to have love from a dog. When she was young, she would place her head between his front paws when he was laying down, and would feel oh so safe. When Tinker died, the girl found a place to be alone to mourn his loss. The girl vowed she would someday have a dog to show her children what it is to have love from a dog.
